    {
      "text": "Warriors of Fate, known in Japan as Tenchi wo Kurau 2: Sekiheki no Tatakai, is a 1992 beat 'em up video game developed and published by Capcom for arcades. It is the second video game based on the Tenchi wo Kurau manga, following 1989's Dynasty Wars. It was ported to the Sega Saturn and PlayStation in 1996. Capcom later included an emulated version of the arcade original as part of Capcom Arcade Stadium and Capcom Beat 'Em Up Bundle.",
